issue.title: Fix a buffer reuse bug in allocation_planner.cc

repository.name: onnxruntime
repository.description: ONNX Runtime: cross-platform, high performance ML inferencing and training accelerator

issue.body:
**Description**: 

Fix a buffer reuse bug in allocation_planner.cc

Resolve #7633

I will add the model to our model tests.

**Motivation and Context**
- Why is this change required? What problem does it solve?
- If it fixes an open issue, please link to the issue here.

body:
@snnn - I guess you want to paste it in https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/issues/7633 :-)

@TomWildenhain-Microsoft - looks like enhancement to me. 

2021-05-11 07:13:50.043565566 [W:onnxruntime:, graph.cc:1074 Graph] Initializer truncation:0 appears in graph inputs and will not be treated as constant value/weight. This may prevent some of the graph optimizations, like const folding. Move it out of graph inputs if there is no need to override it, by either re-generating the model with latest exporter/converter or with the tool onnxruntime/tools/python/remove_initializer_from_input.py.
2021-05-11 07:13:50.043692261 [W:onnxruntime:, graph.cc:3184 CleanUnusedInitializers] Removing initializer 'truncation:0'. It is not used by any node and should be removed from the model.

onnxruntime.capi.onnxruntime_pybind11_state.InvalidArgument: [ONNXRuntimeError] : 2 : INVALID_ARGUMENT : Invalid Feed Input Name:truncation:0

The backend code is expecting just 1 input based on the model you defined, thus giving you the message above. When running the session. I guess the python code could further enhanced to check the input before calling the run() in onnxruntime_inference_collection.py

Adding @thiagocrepaldi / @skottmckay for more comments if any
